OL,3,CTwelfth of July celebrations begin
OL,5,FThe parades mark the 334th anniversary
OL,6,Fof the Battle of the Boyne, when the
OL,7,FProtestant King William of Orange
OL,8,Ftriumphed over the Catholic King James.
OL,10,FWhile most of the bonfires pass off
OL,11,Fwithout incident, several have become
OL,12,Fthe focus of contention due to the
OL,13,Fplacing of flags, effigies and
OL,14,Felection posters on the structures
OL,15,Fbefore they are ignited.
OL,17,FThere was widespread condemnation
OL,18,Fafter a bonfire in Moygashel, Co
OL,19,FTyrone, featured a replica of a mosque.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/3
